<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="frexp" id="frexp">frexp</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Sintaxe:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">frexp</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> num, <span class="kw4">int</span><span class="sy2">*</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

A função frexp() é usada para decompor num em duas partes: uma mantissa
entre 0.5 e 1 (devolvida pela função) e um expoente devolvido em exp.
A notação científica funciona assim:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">     num <span class="sy1">=</span> mantissa <span class="sy2">*</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="nu0">2</span> <span class="sy3">^</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span></pre>
<p>
O C++ também fornece as seguintes formas sobre-carregadas (overload):

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">frexp</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">float</span> num, <span class="kw4">int</span><span class="sy2">*</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// igual a frexpf() em C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">frexp</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> num, <span class="kw4">int</span><span class="sy2">*</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// igual a frexpl() em C99</span></pre>
<p>
Tópicos Relacionados: <a href="ldexp" class="wikilink1" title="br-pt:numeric:c:ldexp">ldexp</a>, <a href="modf" class="wikilink1" title="br-pt:numeric:c:modf">modf</a>

</p>

